Answer:
gpt_response: The SMILES expression of a molecule represents its unique structural arrangement using a series of characters. In the case of C8H17NOS, the SMILES expression would be "CCNCCCCC(=O)O." This notation succinctly conveys the connectivity of carbon (C), hydrogen (H), nitrogen (N), oxygen (O), and sulfur (S) atoms in the molecule, as well as the double bond present in the carbonyl group. It is a valuable tool for computational chemistry and allows for easy comparison of molecular structures.
